name: Anuradha
about: A brother is a friend who protects you and is always with you but I lost my brother who loved me so much. I was shattered and depressed after that. It was hard but I pulled out myself and started with the new chapter where I recall that if my brother would have been alive and seen me like this, he would have been disappointed. So I should be living a happy life. I believe that my brother is always beside me as a guardian angel. Nothing will take away the memories of my brother. Let's get connected to share what you are going through I will listen to you without any judgment. I wish to be a good friend to you in your bad and good times.

name: Kruti
about: I had been through a very difficult time in my adolescence, and no one had ever supported me. I became depressed as a result of a toxic relationship I had with a boy I had been dating for 5 years. I was dealing with a caste problem at the same time. No one was present during my breakup face. Nobody stood by me. But I want you to know that you are not alone. I am here to listen, assist, and heal. I don't want anyone else to go through what I did! Take one step forward and let's talk about you and your issues. You are not alone!

name: Rashi
about: I'm Rashi – an empathetic soul with a radiant and jolly spirit. Amidst despair, my non-judgmental nature provides solace, creating a safe space for expression. A skilled listener, I delve into the intricacies of emotions, offering genuine understanding and support. I bring forth a tapestry of comforting words and wisdom. My friendly demeanor invites openness, encouraging others to share their deepest feelings. Conversations with me transcend the mundane, becoming beautiful and enduring journeys. With my empathetic touch, despair turns into shared experiences, fostering connections that withstand the test of time. Trust in me as your confidante, where every conversation is a testament to the strength of human connection💙🌻

name: Vimala
about: Dear Anonymous,Understanding other humans are very difficult, weather your friend, boyfriend, girlfriend sometimes even parents. but you can understand yourself you can love yourself you know your worth and who you're. don't loose hope on you. kindly connect with me let's find out your inner strength.

name: Mahi
about: I felt broken, lonely, depressed, and had suicidal thoughts every day, and didn't know what to do next. I was pushed into such a situation by my parents. They always wanted to seek control over me and wanted me to be under their dependency. My parents ignored my feelings, didn't respect my physical or emotional boundaries, judged me, and held me in lower esteem than others. I wanted to live my life since I was tired of living according to their wishes. I slowly started to set boundaries, and this helped me to connect with people and build confidence. Now, I can say I'm becoming stronger by doing what I like and living my life on my own terms. That's my story! Would love to hear yours too!

name: Jyoti
about:
Life has a way of knocking you down, and when it does, it's easy to get lost in the pain. But there's no need to let that happen—you have the power to move forward.

The truth is, unless you let go (and even then, it might take some time), you cannot move forward. Moving on is hard but it's the right thing to do. Since high school, I've been in a relationship but my family was totally against it. But I fought with them and we moved to college together. After 2 months, I found out that he was cheating on me and it made me feel like I wasn't good enough but I confronted him and broke up with him. Since then, I worked on myself a lot and didn't let pain ruin me. It took me a lot of time and courage but today, I have realized that I was always a good partner whereas he wasn't the one for me.

I just want to help you realize that you're enough and don't let one break up define you! Let's get connected!

name: Riya
about: hello my lovely users, I’ve been cheated by someone, and I also lost many friends in my life..when I needed them most they left me. now I’m gradually learning how to be happy in my own vibe..❤️

name: Smita
about:
I like talking to people and listening to their problems and giving them solutions so that they remain stress free and happy.

I am a good listener because Listening is the ability to accurately receive and interpret messages in the communication process.

I love communication between two people.
So Listening, however, requires more than that: it requires focus and concentrated effort, both mental and sometimes physical as well.

name: Shireen
about: I am someone who deals with a plethora of mental illnesses such as Borderline Personality Disorder, Bipolar Affective Disorder, Obsessive Compulsive Disorder, Anxiety, and Depression. Dealing with all these issues is a struggle daily, however, one time I was struggling severely with self-harm and suicidal ideation. I was so scared that I could not even ask for help. During that time I was stuck in a freeze response and felt out of control of my actions and body. That time I talked to myself and I somehow was able to convince myself using all the coping techniques I had acquired through years of therapy. I was able to not give in to those thoughts and not act upon the ideations I had about ending my life. Even though it seems simple to pen down into words but in essence it took every ounce of life in me not to end it all.

name: Meena
about:
I had a love story from my college days. He only proposed me. Since we are in love, I'm the only person who gave love. And the other person won't gave anything. He was like a monsoon rain. So rarely he gave a attention to me. I can handle with him like relationships were like this only. So I couldn't give up on him. Finally, he broke up nth time with me.
I was done with him before 4 months.
It's a tragedic one. Finally I accept the reality.

name: Krishna
about:
Loneliness is defined as the absence of connection. I was alone, and no one aided me during my difficult times.
I was emotionally depressed when I realized the people I cared about completely rejected me. But all of the negativity and blame helped to boost my confidence and help me overcome my depression.
There are people out there just like me who need someone to talk to and a heart to understand them. I may not be able to solve all of your problems, but I can guarantee that you will not have to face them alone.
The ability to become a good listener is the key to a happy friendship. Let us be friends!

name: Preeti
about:
My best friend was depressed due to her relationship. I used to see her suffering from loneliness. She was supposed to focus on her career but was badly stuck and broken. She used to skip meals and lock herself in the room for hours. I tried to help her and made her understand the importance of life. I used to sit with her, cheer her and listen to her for hours. It took a lot of time, but she got healed. This made me believe time never remains the same and talking to someone will surely give you purpose to live your life. And I m glad I was there for my friend. The satisfaction I get from helping others is beyond what I can ever ask for. 
Let's connect.

name: Sharvari
about: I was in a 4 year long toxic relationship with my boyfriend. After break up it took me a lot of time to understand the value of myself and how to love myself and move on in my life. After counseling sessions I started building confidence in myself and started feeling better. I also got the vision to see life positively💫💖

name: Bincy
about:
I probably love telling how I live the life I live now. During all my childhood , I was physically and emotionally abused by my narcissistic mother , who was a single parent. Everyday I could find blood in my body , blue coloured patches in my body and what not. All that narcissists want is control. That explains why I was devalued , guilt tripped , gaslighted , tortured and even sexually assaulted by my own parent.  Even my fights to sleep alone at night was in vain. I would even be beaten up in my sleep.  He used to hit me with knife , throw big stones at me , bruise me with keys and would not even let me close the door while taking bath. My neighbours  used to say that she was mentally unstable. But no ! She was just narcissistic. Due to her guilt tripping , I always felt that I am a horrible person and that I shouldn't hurt my mother by being a stupid and disobedient child. She used to guilt trip me by saying that she sacrificed her life for me by not remarrying and working so hard for me. She also used to take me to many counselling centres and retreat centres and all of them used to tell me that I should obey my mother and not be so arrogant. She even made my teachers and school authorites tell me that I should obey my mother and not be a brat and a spoiled child. My whole childhood I believed that I wasn't good enough. My insecurities were very evident and my constant need for attention made me alone , with no friends. I was often bullied by my friends too because I was annoying. I was very insecure and was attention seeking. My mother would scare my friends away from me and made me stay away from all relatives and neighbours.  My change began when I had no other entertainments but books. I was very obssessed with psychology and spirituality. I tried very hard to understand what my problem was. By that time I had CPTSD and that caused me to have no memories. I'M SO THANKFUL FOR MY PAST AND I WILL NOT TRADE MY PAST FOR ANYTHING ELSE IN THE WHOLE WORLD. I'M SOO HAPPY FOR EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENED IN MY PAST . WITHOUT MY PAINFUL BUT BEAUTIFUL PAST , I WOULD NOT HAVE THE STRENGTH I HAVE TODAY.
I was very obssessed with psychology and spirituality and used it to understand what my problem was. I gradually realised everything that I was going through. By that time , I had gained uncanny people skills , empathy and the ability to persuade anybody , specially , the ability to detect narcissists and deal with them because I had many narcissitic people who had romantic interests in me. 
Once I understood what was going on in my life , I realised my strength . After that , whenever my mother tried to attack me , I would charge back fiercely and would hurt her , the way she did to me. Now she is very scared of me and does not dare to touch me. She can't even guilt trip ne anymore because , I was never her daughter. I was an investment for her. She worked hard to educate me only because she wants ne to work and earn for her till she dies.  I stopped giving her any control over me. I stoppped taking any BS from her. I also dress the way I want and she has no say in it. I also didn't have to care about what the neighbours think of me because my mother had already made me believe that they hate me but they don't lol.
Changing my lifestyle was pretty easy for me because I had already gone through the worst so I didn't have any fear anymore.  
One day I just started doing whatever I want , and whenever she questioned , I charged at her till she realised that she has no control over me. 
Now , even when I have to leave for three or four day trips with my friends , I don't ask her. I just tell her and leave. Now everything is peaceful at home. She stays at her place. 
The realisation that I'm alone , sharpened my decision making abilities and I do exercises like meditation and pranayama to heighten my intuition.
